<div id="comment_status_64968347" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64968347" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64968347" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64968347" name="comment_link_64968347" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23530223&amp;cid=64968347" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64968347)" >Re: Yay misery!</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64968347" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64968347); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~newcastlejon">newcastlejon</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~newcastlejon">( 1483695 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64968347">		
		on Sunday November 24, 2024 @08:56AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23530223&amp;cid=64968347">#64968347</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64968347">If I show up to work at a factory and the machinery is all off because of a power cut or whatever then I can't be sacked for not working. That would be a fast track to the business losing an employment tribunal. Likewise, if I have a desk job and the office doesn't have enough workstations I can't be sacked for not working. Just packing up and going home <i>would</i> be reason enough for dismissal but if you run a business where your bad planning leaves your employees unable to do their jobs you can't really complain when you turn up to the office and find half your staff milling around with their thumbs up their arses. You can make them redundant, with all the attendant costs, but you can't just sack them.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64968347">
