		<div id="comment_body_64968339"><p><div class="quote"><p>I would be concerned.</p><p>If there are managers making such decisions as this, and such miscalculations whether by design or ignorance I would begin to look for another investment partner.</p></div><p>Yours is the most intelligent post in this topic so far. </p><p>

We've had people saying that they should all go to work, and do nothing. </p><p>
We've had people who believe that it isn't possible to have all the employees at a location, despite humanity having done that for a long, long time.  </p><p>

Meanwhile, you note that you would look for another job - that is the correct and intelligent response. </p><p>

If it is a deal breaker for people that they will never work anywhere outside their house, then that is the sort of work<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64968339">

